TITLE: NASA's Artemis I mission is bound for the moon: Second launch attempt threatened by fuel leak
SUMMARY: NASA scrapped its first attempt to launch Artemis I earlier this week. Saturday's new launch for the moon mission is facing some fuel leak issues.<div class="fbz_enclosure" style="clear: left;">

TITLE: Mississippi police say pilot threatened to crash small plane into Walmart; Gov. warns residents to 'be on alert'
SUMMARY: Gov. Tate Reeves warned Tupelo, Mississippi, residents to "be on alert" after an airplane pilot threatened to crash into a Walmart, police said.<div class="fbz_enclosure" style="clear: left;">
